## 1. Module Definition

### 1.1 Precise Responsibility

This module group is responsible for:

1. **Acquiring video** from each phone at the highest quality the PWA environment allows, locally on the device, with zero network interference during capture.
2. **Rendering a ground-truth timing reference** (the Visual Metronome) on the laptop screen, which is physically visible to both cameras throughout the recording.
3. **Recovering the true per-frame timestamps** for every frame of every camera, correcting for inter-camera shutter phase offset and per-device clock drift, producing a single authoritative `sync.json` file.

### 1.2 Non-Goals

- Real-time synchronisation of cameras during recording (not required; all sync is post-hoc)
- Frame-accurate start/stop triggers (cameras may start and stop at different moments; sync handles this)
- Lossless video compression beyond 100 Mbps (not needed; compression artefacts are negligible at this bitrate)
- Live frame transmission to PC during recording (the WebRTC preview stream serves framing only; no data is extracted from it)
- Synchronisation accuracy below 0.5ms (not required by physics accuracy budget)

### 1.3 Precise Inputs / Outputs

#### Inputs

| Name                   | Type                       | Units   | Shape  | Constraints                                                                        |
| ---------------------- | -------------------------- | ------- | ------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `camera_stream`        | `MediaStream`              | —       | scalar | Rear camera, `resizeMode: 'none'`                                                  |
| `experiment_id`        | `string`                   | —       | scalar | UUID v4, provided by Node.js at session start                                      |
| `recording_duration_s` | `float32`                  | seconds | scalar | Set by user; ≥ 10s recommended                                                     |
| `frames_dir_cam{n}`    | `string` (filesystem path) | —       | scalar | `/experiments/{id}/frames/cam{n}/` — populated by ffmpeg before sync analysis runs |
| `frame_count_cam{n}`   | `uint32`                   | frames  | scalar | Number of PNG files in `frames_dir_cam{n}`                                         |

#### Outputs

| Name                              | Type      | Units  | Shape  | Constraints                                        |
| --------------------------------- | --------- | ------ | ------ | -------------------------------------------------- |
| `sync.json`                       | JSON file | —      | —      | Schema defined in §0.3                             |
| `timestamp_ms[cam_id][frame_idx]` | `float64` | ms     | `[N]`  | Monotonically increasing; frame 0 of cam0 = 0.0 ms |
| `true_fps[cam_id]`                | `float64` | Hz     | scalar | Expected range: 28.0–62.0                          |
| `phase_offset_ms[cam_id]`         | `float64` | ms     | scalar | Relative to reference camera (cam0 = 0.0)          |
| `fit_residual_rms_px[cam_id]`     | `float64` | pixels | scalar | Quality metric; alert if > 1.5px                   |
| `sync_accuracy_ms`                | `float64` | ms     | scalar | = `phase_offset_ms` uncertainty (1σ)               |

