  "dot_speed_px_per_frame": {
    "cam0": 19.843,
    "cam1": 19.839
  }
}
```

**Time representation:** All `timestamp_ms` values are float64 milliseconds. The epoch is defined as: **frame 0 of the reference camera (`cam0`) = 0.0 ms**. All other timestamps are offsets from this epoch. Negative timestamps are valid (if cam1's shutter precedes cam0 frame 0).

**Coordinate system:** Dot X-position is measured in pixels from the left edge of the frame. Origin = left edge = 0. Right edge = `frame_width - 1`. Y-axis is not used in sync analysis (dot is tracked as a 1D horizontal position).

