## 5. Execution Model

### 5.1 Phone PWA (Subcomponents A, B, C)

| Aspect             | Detail                                                                                        |
| ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Invocation type    | Async/event-driven                                                                            |
| Trigger            | User taps "Record" button in Experiment Recording screen                                      |
| Concurrency        | Single-threaded JavaScript; `MediaRecorder` runs on browser's media thread (separate from JS) |
| Recording duration | Unbounded; stops on user tap or session timeout                                               |
| Upload trigger     | Automatically on `stopRecording()` completion                                                 |
| Upload concurrency | Sequential if two phones; both upload independently to Node.js                                |

State machine for the phone PWA recording flow:

```
IDLE
  → [User taps Record] → RECORDING
RECORDING
  → [ondataavailable] → accumulate chunk (stays in RECORDING)
  → [User taps Stop] → STOPPING
STOPPING
  → [onstop fires] → UPLOADING
UPLOADING
  → [onprogress] → update progress bar (stays in UPLOADING)
  → [upload complete] → DONE
  → [upload error] → ERROR (user can retry)
DONE / ERROR (terminal states)
```

### 5.2 Laptop Browser Metronome (Subcomponent D)

| Aspect               | Detail                                                                                               |
| -------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Invocation type      | `requestAnimationFrame` loop (asynchronous, display-sync'd)                                          |
| Trigger              | Metronome starts when user enters Experiment Recording screen; stops on navigation away              |
| Concurrency          | Single `requestAnimationFrame` chain; no workers needed                                              |
| Timing model         | Wall-clock elapsed time from `performance.now()`; frame drops do not affect dot position correctness |
| Real-time constraint | Soft: each `rAF` callback must complete in < 5ms (rendering only; no computation)                    |

### 5.3 Python Sync Analysis (Subcomponent E)

| Aspect                 | Detail                                                                                            |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Invocation type        | Synchronous within gRPC handler; streaming progress updates via gRPC server streaming             |
| Trigger                | Node.js calls `RunSyncAnalysis` gRPC after ffmpeg extraction completes for both cameras           |
| Concurrency            | Single-process; SAM2 uses PyTorch multi-thread internally (controlled by `torch.set_num_threads`) |
| Per-camera parallelism | Cameras processed sequentially (not in parallel) to avoid VRAM contention                         |
| Estimated duration     | 1–5 minutes per camera for 60s recording at 30fps (1800 frames × ~100ms SAM2/frame)               |
| Buffering              | No frame buffering required; frames read from disk on demand by SAM2                              |

