[gRPC stream] SyncStatus { stage: "complete" } → Node.js → WebSocket → UI
```

### 6.2 What is Retained vs Discarded

| Data                            | Retained?                | Location                           |
| ------------------------------- | ------------------------ | ---------------------------------- |
| Raw video file (`.webm`/`.mp4`) | Yes (permanent)          | `/experiments/{id}/raw/`           |
| Extracted PNG frames            | Yes (permanent)          | `/experiments/{id}/frames/cam{n}/` |
| `MediaRecorder` Blob chunks     | Discarded after upload   | Phone RAM                          |
| SAM2 inference state            | Discarded after tracking | Python RAM / VRAM                  |
| `DotTrackingResult` arrays      | Discarded after fit      | Python RAM                         |
| `LinearFitResult`               | Stored in `sync.json`    | Disk                               |
| `timestamp_ms` arrays           | Stored in `sync.json`    | Disk                               |

### 6.3 Clock / State Persistence

- The metronome has no persistent state — it is stateless across sessions.
- `sync.json` is the only persistent state produced by this module group.
- `sync.json` is consumed (read-only) by the Physics Engine and Ball Tracking modules. They must never modify it.
- If sync analysis is re-run (e.g., after user re-frames the dot seed), `sync.json` is overwritten atomically (write to temp file, then rename).

