### 7.3 Exact Call Sequence (Happy Path)

```
1. React mounts Experiment Recording screen
   → calls VisualMetronomeRenderer.start() [laptop canvas]
   → calls acquireCamera() for each phone

2. User presses Record
   → Node.js WebSocket: "RECORDING_STARTED" broadcast to all phones
   → Each phone: recorder.start(1000)

3. [Recording in progress: dot animating on laptop screen, cameras capturing]

4. User presses Stop
   → Node.js WebSocket: "RECORDING_STOPPED" broadcast to all phones
   → Each phone: recorder.stop()
   → VisualMetronomeRenderer.stop()

5. Each phone: VideoUploader.upload()
   POST /api/upload-video → Node.js

6. Node.js: stores file, spawns ffmpeg
   ffmpeg -i cam{n}.webm -vsync 0 frames/cam{n}/frame_%06d.png
   → on ffmpeg exit: WebSocket "FFMPEG_COMPLETE" { cameraId, frameCount }

7. Node.js: when BOTH cameras complete ffmpeg extraction:
   → gRPC call: RunSyncAnalysis({ experiment_id, camera_ids: ["cam0", "cam1"] })

8. Python: run_sync_analysis()
   → stream SyncStatus { stage: "dot_tracking", camera_id: "cam0", progress: 0..1 }
   → stream SyncStatus { stage: "dot_tracking", camera_id: "cam1", progress: 0..1 }
   → stream SyncStatus { stage: "linear_fit", ... }
   → write sync.json
   → stream SyncStatus { stage: "complete" }

9. Node.js: forward SyncStatus events via WebSocket to React UI
   React UI: display sync quality report (R², residual RMS, sync accuracy)

10. React UI: transition to Ball Selection screen (next module group)
```

